From f8edc3e16a25901c0b180bc13b52107253821f1c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Elias Ellison <elias.ellison@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 23:34:36 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] [inductor] Triton finalize kernel for multi-output
 split-reduction sums (1.14x on affected kernels)

When a multi-output split reduction saves partial sums to a workspace, the
finalize step previously fell back to ATen's generic .sum(dim=0) over the
[nsplit, rnumel] workspace view. This emits a dedicated 2D Triton finalize
kernel instead (tiles both the tile and column dimensions, coalesced loads,
atomic_add accumulation into a zero-initialized output), which beats the
generic ATen reduce on every affected shape.

Applies to reduction_type == 'sum' on CUDA python-wrapper builds; all other
reduction types / cpp_wrapper keep the ATen fallback.

Measured (B200, 158-model corpus): 1.14x kernel geomean over the 52 affected
sum_sum_sum (3-level multi-output split-reduction) repros, 48/52 faster,
0 regressions, best 1.46x (XLNet); +0.95pp e2e geomean on the 29 touched
TRAIN models.

written with claude code
